---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "KitchenAid Range Hood Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "KitchenAid range hood repair across SoCal. KVUB, KVWB, KXU professional series. Whirlpool family platform. BHGS #A49573. $89 dx waived with repair.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/kitchenaid-range-hood-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What KitchenAid range hood models are most common in LA?",
    a: "Four active formats in the US KitchenAid hood lineup. <b>KVUC Commercial-Style undercabinet</b>, KVUC600KSS 30-inch, 585 CFM, pro-style aesthetic with commercial-grade mesh filters; the flagship positioning against Bosch 800 Series + Viking VWH entry. <b>KVUB Convertible undercabinet</b>, KVUB600DSS 30-inch 600 CFM, KVUB400GSS 30-inch 400 CFM, KVUB606DSS 36-inch 600 CFM; convertible means ducted OR recirculating with charcoal filter for apartments without venting. <b>Wall-mount chimney</b>, 400 / 600 CFM, 30-36 inch widths, stainless / black stainless / matte black finishes. <b>Island mount</b>, 600 CFM, 36 and 42 inch widths. Plus downdraft and microwave-OTR combo variants. All route through Whirlpool's Benton Harbor Michigan parts chain alongside Whirlpool / Maytag / Amana / Jenn-Air."
  },
  {
    q: "KVUC Commercial-Style, what makes it actually commercial-style vs standard undercabinet?",
    a: "Three meaningful differences vs standard KVUB. <b>(1) 585 CFM motor output</b>, higher than standard 400 CFM undercabinet; comparable to Bosch 500 Series flagship. <b>(2) Commercial-grade mesh filters</b>, larger surface area, dishwasher-safe, handle high-BTU cooking better than standard grease filters. <b>(3) Pro-style aesthetic</b>, knob controls instead of touch-panel, industrial stainless mesh, taller chassis height. Service implication: KVUC is built for higher-duty-cycle cooking (LA kitchens with Wolf or Viking ranges paired with a KitchenAid hood), and the larger filters need cleaning every 4-6 weeks in high-use kitchens rather than the 8-12 week interval for standard undercabinet. Motor replacement on KVUC runs $280-$440 vs $180-$280 on standard KVUB, larger motor, higher cost."
  },
  {
    q: "KitchenAid hood won't exhaust vs won't recirculate, convertible confusion?",
    a: "<b>KVUB Convertible</b> means the hood can run in two modes, <b>ducted</b> (exhausts air outside through ductwork in the wall/roof) OR <b>recirculating</b> (passes air through a charcoal filter and returns it to the kitchen). Common confusion: customers call saying \"hood isn't venting properly\" when actually the hood was installed in recirculating mode because there's no ductwork, and the charcoal filter is saturated (needs quarterly replacement, $30-$80). We check install mode first during diagnostic, if it's a ducted install with poor airflow, that's a motor or vent issue; if it's recirculating with saturated filter, that's a $30 consumable not a repair. Ducted-mode issues are standard wall-mount diagnostic; recirculating-mode issues usually resolve with filter replacement + cleaning service."
  },
  {
    q: "Whirlpool-family parts cross-fit, how much does it save on KitchenAid hood service?",
    a: "Whirlpool Corporation's five-brand family (Whirlpool + KitchenAid + Maytag + Amana + Jenn-Air) shares mechanical parts at the Benton Harbor Michigan parts chain level. For KitchenAid range hoods specifically, <b>turntable-equivalent fan motors, grease-filter hardware, light-assembly LED drivers, door switch / interlock sensors, and some variable-speed controls cross-fit across Whirlpool / Maytag / Amana undercabinet + wall-mount hoods</b>. Control boards and front-panel aesthetics stay brand-specific (KitchenAid Architect II trim won't cross-fit a Whirlpool chassis even if the motor shares a part number). Practical impact: when a specific KitchenAid SKU is backordered, a Whirlpool or Maytag cross-reference often ships same-day with an identical chassis. Our LA service inventory leverages this regularly for shorter wait times. See <a href='/brands/whirlpool-range-hood-repair/'>Whirlpool range hood</a> · <a href='/brands/maytag-range-hood-repair/'>Maytag range hood</a>."
  },
  {
    q: "KitchenAid matched-suite kitchen, hood + range + dishwasher + fridge all KA?",
    a: "Common spec in LA premium kitchens, KitchenAid range + KitchenAid range hood + KitchenAid dishwasher + KitchenAid refrigerator as a matched suite. The suite coherence is the main reason KitchenAid ships a broad hood lineup (KVUC commercial-style positioning against pro-style ranges, KVUB convertible for standard installs), it's defensive against customers defecting to Bosch or Thermador for the hood slot when they already committed to KitchenAid elsewhere. Service-side, matched-suite kitchens get diagnostic efficiency: one technician can service multiple KitchenAid appliances in a single call, parts cross-fit within the Whirlpool family, and firmware on SmartThinQ-connected KitchenAid appliances pairs via the same app. Tell us at booking if you have other KitchenAid appliances with issues, we combine service calls when it makes sense."
  },
  {
    q: "What does KitchenAid range hood repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic $89 waived with repair. Typical KitchenAid bands: <b>KVUC Commercial-Style</b> 585 CFM motor $280–$440; control panel knob assembly $240–$380. <b>KVUB Convertible</b> motor $180–$280; charcoal filter (recirculating mode, quarterly consumable) $30–$80; grease-filter cleaning service $60–$120 (often sufficient, no part). <b>Wall-mount / island</b> control board $280–$420; LED driver $160–$260. <b>Shared across formats</b>: grease-filter latch $100–$180; door switch / interlock $100–$180; variable-speed switch $120–$200; light socket $40–$120. Whirlpool-family parts cross-fit via Benton Harbor MI regularly shortens wait on backordered SKUs."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, KitchenAid Range Hood Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$"
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "KitchenAid Range Hood Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "KitchenAid range hood repair across LA, KVUC commercial-style 585 CFM, KVUB convertible 400/600 CFM undercabinet, wall-mount chimney + island mount + downdraft + OTR combo formats. Whirlpool family (since 1986) parts chain via Benton Harbor Michigan. Matched-suite integration with KitchenAid range + dishwasher + refrigerator. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "KitchenAid", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/kitchenaid/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "KitchenAid Range Hood Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>KitchenAid range hood service?</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › KitchenAid › Range Hood Repair</div>
    <h1>KitchenAid Range Hood Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">KitchenAid (Whirlpool Corporation since 1986; Hobart origin 1919) ships a full US range-hood lineup: KVUC commercial-style 30-inch undercabinet at 585 CFM (flagship positioning against Bosch 800 and Viking VWH entry), KVUB convertible undercabinet 400-600 CFM (ducted or recirculating for apartments without venting), wall-mount chimney 400-600 CFM across 30-36 inch widths, 36/42-inch island mounts, downdraft variants, and microwave-OTR combo units. All route through Whirlpool's Benton Harbor Michigan parts chain alongside the four sibling brands (Whirlpool + Maytag + Amana + Jenn-Air), which means mechanical parts cross-fit across the family regularly and backordered KitchenAid SKUs often ship same-day with a sibling brand label. For LA, KitchenAid hoods are a matched-suite cornerstone in premium kitchens where the range + dishwasher + refrigerator are already KA. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>KVUC commercial-style 585 CFM + KVUB convertible + wall + island + downdraft + OTR</b></li>
      <li><b>Convertible mode</b>, ducted OR recirculating with charcoal filter</li>
      <li><b>Whirlpool family since 1986</b>, cross-fits Whirlpool / Maytag / Amana / Jenn-Air hood parts</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What KitchenAid range hood repair costs in LA</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>KVUC 585 CFM motor (commercial-style)</td><td>$280 – $440</td><td>Flagship tier</td></tr>
      <tr><td>KVUC knob-control panel</td><td>$240 – $380</td><td>Pro-style control assembly</td></tr>
      <tr><td>KVUB convertible motor</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>Standard undercabinet</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Charcoal filter (recirculating mode)</td><td>$30 – $80</td><td>Quarterly consumable</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Grease-filter cleaning service</td><td>$60 – $120</td><td>Often resolves, no part</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Wall / island control board</td><td>$280 – $420</td><td>Touch-panel electronics</td></tr>
      <tr><td>LED driver</td><td>$160 – $260</td><td>Task lighting</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Grease-filter latch / interlock</td><td>$100 – $180</td><td>Safety switch</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Variable-speed switch</td><td>$120 – $200</td><td>Rotary or touch</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Related: <a href="/brands/kitchenaid-refrigerator-repair/">KitchenAid brand hub</a> · <a href="/brands/kitchenaid-range-repair/">KitchenAid range</a> · <a href="/brands/kitchenaid-dishwasher-repair/">KitchenAid dishwasher</a> · <a href="/brands/kitchenaid-refrigerator-repair/">KitchenAid refrigerator</a> · <a href="/brands/kitchenaid-microwave-repair/">KitchenAid microwave (OTR combo)</a> · <a href="/brands/whirlpool-range-hood-repair/">Whirlpool range hood (family peer)</a> · <a href="/brands/maytag-range-hood-repair/">Maytag range hood (family peer)</a> · <a href="/services/range-hood-repair/">Range hood repair (service hub)</a> · <a href="/price-list/range-hood-repair-cost/">Range hood repair cost</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Matched-suite KitchenAid kitchen, the install-base reality</h2>
    <p>In LA premium kitchen remodels, KitchenAid ships as a matched suite more often than any single brand except the luxury heavyweights (Wolf, Sub-Zero, Thermador). The standard spec looks like this: KitchenAid range + KitchenAid range hood + KitchenAid dishwasher + KitchenAid refrigerator + sometimes KitchenAid microwave OTR combo. The range hood slot is the one KitchenAid most often loses to Bosch or Broan when customers want a budget hood, which is exactly why KitchenAid builds the KVUC commercial-style positioning to fight for that slot with a credible 585 CFM pro-style offering.</p>
    <p>Service-side, matched-suite kitchens offer diagnostic efficiency: one technician can cover multiple KitchenAid appliances in a single call, parts cross-fit within the Whirlpool family (Whirlpool + KitchenAid + Maytag + Amana + Jenn-Air mechanical cross-fit via Benton Harbor MI), and firmware on SmartThinQ-connected KitchenAid appliances pairs via the same Whirlpool Connected Kitchen app. When you call for KitchenAid hood service, mention any other KitchenAid appliances that need attention, we combine calls when it makes sense.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>KitchenAid range hood repair, frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>KitchenAid range hood service? Call the branch closest to your home.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance repair in Los Angeles, Orange County, Ventura County. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
  </div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  body { color: var(--text); } .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; } .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin: 12px 0 20px; color: var(--black); }
  h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--black); }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .call-banner { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 10px 0; }
  .call-banner .wrap { display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .call-banner .phone-lg { color:#fff; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: underline; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 42px 0 56px; } .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .lede { font-size: 1.06rem; color: #d7d7d7; max-width: 680px; }
  .hero .crumb { color: #9a9a9a; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 6px; } .hero .crumb a { color: #c9c9c9; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
  .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; } .btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #fff; }
  .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #c9c9c9; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-facts li { padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #222; } .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: 0; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 0; }
  .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 56px 0; } .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 14px; background: #fff; }
  .price-table th, .price-table td { text-align: left; padding: 11px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .price-table th { background: var(--black); color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .small { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.92rem; margin-top: 12px; }
  .faq { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .faq summary { font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; padding: 4px 0; } .faq p { margin: 8px 0 0; }
  .cta-bottom { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 48px 0; } .cta-bottom h2 { color: #fff; } .cta-bottom p { color: #c9c9c9; }
  .float-call { position: fixed; bottom: 18px; right: 18px; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 18px; border-radius: 40px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.28); z-index: 50; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; } .float-call { padding: 11px 14px; font-size: 0.88rem; } .trust-bar .wrap { gap: 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; } }
</style>
